@node "Preface" "Preface"
Hello & Welcome to the Lionel: Raiders of The Lost Chessboard Guide..

I am your host, JAZZ and I'm just going to tell you a little bit about the
game and what have you, it's basically a simple game, all you have to do is
guide Lionel around a series of 50 level's and you've completed it.. Easy!
But I'll go into that more in detail in the other sections of this guide, I
just wanted to say thank you for purchasing this game or downloading it and
taking the time to play it.. It mean's a lot to me.

This is only my secound game that I have wrote, the first being the not so
famous Red Dwarf Quiztanaire and it's the first time I have ever coded
anything while being half sober, (well I was sober for the most part) so as
you can imagine quite a bit of work as gone into this game, even if it does
look a bit basic, and it warm's the cockles of my heart to think that
somebody, you, have enjoyed playing this game.

Anyway that's all I wanted to say really, so I will let you get on reading
the rest of this guide... Have Fun...


Jazz
@endnode

@node "Game Menu" "Getting Started"
Once you have loaded Lionel the first thing you will see is a short
introduction sequence and then you will be presented with the main menu with
the following options....

                             @{"StartĀ1ĀPlayerĀGame" link "One Player Game" 0}

                             @{"StartĀ2ĀPlayerĀGame" link "Two Player Game" 0}

                             @{"ViewĀHighscoreĀTable" link "View Hiscore Table" 0}

                                @{"Instructions" link "Instructions" 0}

                                   @{"Options" link "Options Menu" 0}

                                   @{"Credits" link "Credits" 0}

                                    @{"Quit" link "Quit" 0}

                                   @{"Iconify" link "Iconify" 0}

Clicking one of the above buttons will provide more information on the
appropiate sections.

Control of the menu is by joystick or the arrow keys on the keyboard and the
options are selected by pressing fire on the joystick or by pressing the
space bar.
@endnode

@node "One Player Game" "Start 1 Player Game"
This obviously start's the 1 Player version of Lionel, in which you must
guide Lionel round the 50 level's of Innad's castle, seeking the exits and
trying to avoid hitting the wall's and running into dead end's.

Control is either by joystick or keyboard, the joystick control's are
obvious so I won't bother telling about them, but Lionel is controlled with
the arrow keys on the keyboard when you want to use the keyboard...

Pressing escape during the game, will cause the game to return to the main
menu.

Pressing the fire button will cause the game to pause, and pressing the fire
button again will cause the game to unpause, by the same token, pressing the
space bar will do exactly the same thing....
@endnode

@node "Two Player Game" "Start 2 Player Game"
This is the token 2 player version of Lionel, which incidentally is what was
going to be released as Lionel originally, but I changed my mind and wrote
the one player section as the main game.

Player one is controlled via joystick and player two can be controlled by
joystick or keyboard, with the arrow keys again serving as an alternative.

Pressing fire on the joystick will engage turbo mode for the player's, so
you can get that little bit extra speed when required.  The space bar is the
alternative on keys.

While playing the game bonus ball's will appear, collecting these will
result in various bonus's being awarded, but I can't show you them here so
you'll have to look at the 'Instructions' part of the game for more
information.
@endnode

@node "View Hiscore Table" "Hiscore Table"
This bit let's you look at the highscore table (there really was no need for
this text!!)
@endnode

@node "Instructions" "Instructions"
Selecting this option will give you the unbuilt instructions, and will also
show you the bonus ball's that are available in the 2 player mode.
@endnode

@node "Options Menu" "Options Menu"
Selecting this part of the menu you will give you another menu to look at
with the following options, again just click the buttons for more
information...


                               @{"MusicĀOnĀĀOff" link "Music Options" 0}

                               @{"ResetĀHiscore" link "Hiscore Options" 0}

                               @{"EnterĀPassword" link "Password Options" 0}

                            @{"PlayĀDataĀDiskĀLevels" link "Datadisk Options" 0}
@endnode

