@node "Quit" "Don't Touch That Dial"
Don't touch this button!!!!

This one will cause sorrow and loss thoughout the rest of you life, you see
this button will quit the game....

You don't want to do that do you???

Do You???
@endnode

@node "Iconify" "Fool Your Mother"
This option will let you return to workbench, or where ever and let you do
something else, and then let you return to LIONEL when you fancy another
game, dead handy when your supposed to be doing your homework or something
like that....
@endnode

@node "Music Options" "Today Is Going To Be The Day..."
This is for switching the in game music on and off, if switched on then you
lose the rather crap samples, so it's quite possible that it's better
switched on.....

Be the way the ingame music was ripped from Superfrog by Team 17
@endnode

@node "Hiscore Options" "Resetting The Hiscore"
Selecting this will reset the hiscores to the original default settings that
I have come up with, which is only really handy if somebody has beaten your
hiscore and your rather miffed about it...
@endnode

@node "Password Options" "Entering The Password"
Because Lionel does get a bit harder later on in the game, I have come up
with a password system that allows you to restart the game from certain
level's, every 10 to be precise, so selecting this option will allow you to
type in one of those passwords...

In case your wondering, I haven't left any secret messages in this version
of the game, so there's no point in trying to suss any of them out...
@endnode

@node "Datadisk Options" "Using The Datadisk"
This Option Doesn't concern you yet so there's no need to worry about
that... Just pretend it doesn't exist until you see the title LIONEL EXTRA
LEVELS in your favourite PD Supplier's new advert...

By the way, no matter how many time's you press it, it won't do anything..
@endnode

@node "HD Installation" "Installing LIONEL To The Hard Drive"
The installation for Lionel is really quite simple, all you have to do is to
create a drawer for it, and then drag the installer icon from disk 2 into
your new drawer, then double click on the icon, simple eh?

If you do experience any problems, then I suggest checking that you have all
the neccessary librarys in your LIBS: directory on your hard drive against
the ones on disk 1, I didn't set the installer to copy them all across, only
the 'Easylife.Library' so you may have one missing, sorry about that, but
it's better than me wiping over an important library isn't it?
@endnode

